issue.body:
`EventTarget.prototype.removeEventListener` removes a listener even if it has a different `capture`.

```ts
const target = new EventTarget();
const fn = () => {
  fn.called = true;
};
declare const event: string;
target.addEventListener(event, fn, true);
target.removeEventListener(event, fn, false);
target.dispatchEvent(new Event(event));

console.assert(fn.called);
```

The same listener is always removed.

https://github.com/denoland/deno/blob/03e963f57831367a39996c7d88bc9875e97d52d7/ext/web/02_event.js#L1040-L1042

Spec ref: https://dom.spec.whatwg.org/#dom-eventtarget-removeeventlistener

